  "text": "One gets f j C (p) = p |C| P(X j+1 i = 0, i \u2208 N (C)) and by the inclusion-exclusion principle, . It remains to express the density. In Bousquet-M\u00e9lou [CITATION_1] this is done by differentiation of (31). One may also compute this density by computing W n /Z n where W n = (Y n ) 2,2 which corresponds to the contribution of the configurations where the first cell is occupied (in other words, y 1 = y n+1 = 1). With very simple linear algebra, we get W n = (\u03bb n 1 (\u03bb 1 \u2212 1) + \u03bb n 2 (\u03bb 2 \u2212 1))/(\u03bb 2 \u2212 \u03bb 1 ). Since \u03bb 1 > \u03bb 2 ,",
